Start
/ Writes a file with a path-shaped string, reads it back, and confirms the literal
/ string survives the file round-trip ("just round-trip my path" must not regress).
- save "/example/subdir/file.txt" to file 'path_roundtrip.txt'
- read file 'path_roundtrip.txt', write to %readBack%
- assert %readBack% equals "/example/subdir/file.txt", "path string survives the file round-trip"
